iTurbo Boost technology in Core i5/i7 processors temporarily increases		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iclock speeds under heavy workloads. The problem? This performance		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iboost generates significantly more heat—a disaster for thermally		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconstrained MBPs. Bizarrely, Windows often activates Turbo Boost		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iunnecessarily during light tasks, maxing out CPU frequency and		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icreating excessive heat. Thus, we need to disable Turbo Boost. A Core		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ii5 without Turbo Boost still handles most tasks adequately.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
